{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["48-GAL-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "GAL"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Galatians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s Letter to the Galatians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Galatians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Gal \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s Letter to the Galatians \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "GAL 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GAL 1:1"}, "Paul, an apostle\u2014not from men, nor through man, but through Al Masih Isa, and Allah the Father, who raised him from the\ndead\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GAL 1:2"}, "and all the brothers", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d "]}], "caller": "+"}, " who are with me, to the assemblies of Galatia:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GAL 1:3"}, "Grace to you and peace from Allah the Father and our Lord Al Masih Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GAL 1:4"}, "who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us out of this present evil age, according to the will of our Allah\nand Father\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GAL 1:5"}, "to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GAL 1:6"}, "I marvel that you are so quickly deserting him who called you in the grace of Masih to a different \u201cgood news\u201d,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GAL 1:7"}, "but there isn\u2019t another \u201cgood news.\u201d Only there are some who trouble you and want to pervert the Good News of Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GAL 1:8"}, "But even though we, or an angel from heaven, should preach to you any \u201cgood news\u201d other than that which we preached to\nyou, let him be cursed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GAL 1:9"}, "As we have said before, so I now say again: if any man preaches to you any \u201cgood news\u201d other than that which you received,\nlet him be cursed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GAL 1:10"}, "For am I now seeking the favour of men, or of Allah? Or am I striving to please men? For if I were still pleasing men, I\nwouldn\u2019t be a servant of Masih. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GAL 1:11"}, "But I make known to you, brothers, concerning the Good News which was preached by me, that it is not according to man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GAL 1:12"}, "For I didn\u2019t receive it from man, nor was I taught it, but it came to me through revelation of Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GAL 1:13"}, "For you have heard of my way of living in time past in the Jews\u2019 religion, how that beyond measure I persecuted the\nassembly of Allah and ravaged it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GAL 1:14"}, "I advanced in the Jews\u2019 religion beyond many of my own age amongst my countrymen, being more exceedingly zealous for the\ntraditions of my fathers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GAL 1:15"}, "But when it was the good pleasure of Allah, who separated me from my mother\u2019s womb and called me through his grace\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GAL 1:16"}, "to reveal his Son in me, that I might preach him amongst the Gentiles, I didn\u2019t immediately confer with flesh and blood,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GAL 1:17"}, "nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went away into Arabia. Then I returned to\nDamascus. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GAL 1:18"}, "Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to visit Peter, and stayed with him fifteen days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GAL 1:19"}, "But of the other apostles I saw no one except Yaqub, the Lord\u2019s brother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GAL 1:20"}, "Now about the things which I write to you, behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:20\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u1f30\u03b4\u03bf\u1f7a\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " before Allah, I\u2019m not lying. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GAL 1:21"}, "Then I came to the regions of Syria and Cilicia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GAL 1:22"}, "I was still unknown by face to the assemblies of Judea which were in Masih,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GAL 1:23"}, "but they only heard: \u201cHe who once persecuted us now preaches the faith that he once tried to destroy.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GAL 1:24"}, "So they glorified Allah in me. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "GAL 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GAL 2:1"}, "Then after a period of fourteen years I went up again to Jerusalem with Barnabas, taking Titus also with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GAL 2:2"}, "I went up by revelation, and I laid before them the Good News which I preach amongst the Gentiles, but privately before\nthose who were respected, for fear that I might be running, or had run, in vain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GAL 2:3"}, "But not even Titus, who was with me, being a Greek, was compelled to be circumcised.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GAL 2:4"}, "This was because of the false brothers secretly brought in, who stole in to spy out our liberty which we have in Masih\nIsa, that they might bring us into bondage, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GAL 2:5"}, "to whom we gave no place in the way of subjection, not for an hour, that the truth of the Good News might continue with\nyou. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GAL 2:6"}, "But from those who were reputed to be important\u2014whatever they were, it makes no difference to me; Allah doesn\u2019t show\npartiality to man\u2014they, I say, who were respected imparted nothing to me,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GAL 2:7"}, "but to the contrary, when they saw that I had been entrusted with the Good News for the uncircumcised, even as Peter with\nthe Good News for the circumcised\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GAL 2:8"}, "for he who worked through Peter in the apostleship with the circumcised also worked through me with the Gentiles\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GAL 2:9"}, "and when they perceived the grace that was given to me, Yaqub and Cephas and Yuhanna, those who were reputed to be\npillars, gave to Barnabas and me the right hand of fellowship, that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the circumcision.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GAL 2:10"}, "They only asked us to remember the poor\u2014which very thing I was also zealous to do.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GAL 2:11"}, "But when Peter came to Antioch, I resisted him to his face, because he stood condemned.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GAL 2:12"}, "For before some people came from Yaqub, he ate with the Gentiles. But when they came, he drew back and separated himself,\nfearing those who were of the circumcision. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GAL 2:13"}, "And the rest of the Jews joined him in his hypocrisy, so that even Barnabas was carried away with their hypocrisy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GAL 2:14"}, "But when I saw that they didn\u2019t walk uprightly according to the truth of the Good News, I said to Peter before them all,\n\u201cIf you, being a Jew, live as the Gentiles do, and not as the Jews do, why do you compel the Gentiles to live as the Jews do?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GAL 2:15"}, "\u201cWe, being Jews by nature, and not Gentile sinners, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GAL 2:16"}, "yet knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law but through faith in Al Masih Isa, even we believed in\nMasih Isa, that we might be justified by faith in Masih, and not by the works of the law, because no flesh will be justified by\nthe works of the law. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GAL 2:17"}, "But if while we sought to be justified in Masih, we ourselves also were found sinners, is Masih a servant of sin?\nCertainly not! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GAL 2:18"}, "For if I build up again those things which I destroyed, I prove myself a law-breaker.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GAL 2:19"}, "For I, through the law, died to the law, that I might live to Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GAL 2:20"}, "I have been crucified with Masih, and it is no longer I that live, but Masih lives in me. That life which I now live in\nthe flesh, I live by faith in the Son of Allah, who loved me, and gave himself up for me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GAL 2:21"}, "I don\u2019t reject the grace of Allah. For if righteousness is through the law, then Masih died for nothing!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "GAL 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GAL 3:1"}, "Foolish Galatians, who has bewitched you not to obey the truth, before whose eyes Al Masih Isa was openly portrayed\namongst you as crucified? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GAL 3:2"}, "I just want to learn this from you: Did you receive the Spirit by the works of the law, or by hearing of faith?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GAL 3:3"}, "Are you so foolish? Having begun in the Spirit, are you now completed in the flesh?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GAL 3:4"}, "Did you suffer so many things in vain, if it is indeed in vain?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GAL 3:5"}, "He therefore who supplies the Spirit to you and does miracles amongst you, does he do it by the works of the law, or by\nhearing of faith? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GAL 3:6"}, "Even as Ibrahim \u201cbelieved Allah, and it was counted to him for\nrighteousness.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 15:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GAL 3:7"}, "Know therefore that those who are of faith are children of Ibrahim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GAL 3:8"}, "The Scripture, foreseeing that Allah would justify the Gentiles by faith, preached the Good News beforehand to Ibrahim,\nsaying, \u201cIn you all the nations will be blessed.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis\n12:3; 18:18; 22:18"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GAL 3:9"}, "So then, those who are of faith are blessed with the faithful Ibrahim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GAL 3:10"}, "For as many as are of the works of the law are under a curse. For it is written, \u201cCursed is everyone who doesn\u2019t continue\nin all things that are written in the book of the law, to do them.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 27:26"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GAL 3:11"}, "Now that no man is justified by the law before Allah is evident, for, \u201cThe righteous will live by\nfaith.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Habakkuk 2:4"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GAL 3:12"}, "The law is not of faith, but, \u201cThe man who does them will live by\nthem.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Leviticus 18:5"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GAL 3:13"}, "Masih redeemed us from the curse of the law, having become a curse for us. For it is written, \u201cCursed is everyone who\nhangs on a tree,\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 21:23"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GAL 3:14"}, "that the blessing of Ibrahim might come on the Gentiles through Masih Isa, that we might receive the promise of the\nSpirit through faith. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GAL 3:15"}, "Brothers, speaking of human terms, though it is only a man\u2019s covenant, yet when it has been confirmed, no one makes it\nvoid or adds to it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GAL 3:16"}, "Now the promises were spoken to Ibrahim and to his offspring.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " He doesn\u2019t say, \u201cTo descendants", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:16\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seeds"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\u201d, as of many, but as of one, \u201cTo your offspring\u201d,", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["3:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 12:7; 13:15; 24:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, " which is Masih. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GAL 3:17"}, "Now I say this: A covenant confirmed beforehand by Allah in Masih, the law, which came four hundred and thirty years\nafter, does not annul, so as to make the promise of no effect. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GAL 3:18"}, "For if the inheritance is of the law, it is no more of promise; but Allah has granted it to Ibrahim by promise.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GAL 3:19"}, "Then why is there the law? It was added because of transgressions, until the offspring should come to whom the promise\nhas been made. It was ordained through angels by the hand of a mediator.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GAL 3:20"}, "Now a mediator is not between one, but Allah is one. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GAL 3:21"}, "Is the law then against the promises of Allah? Certainly not! For if there had been a law given which could make alive,\nmost certainly righteousness would have been of the law. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GAL 3:22"}, "But the Scripture imprisoned all things under sin, that the promise by faith in Al Masih Isa might be given to those who\nbelieve. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GAL 3:23"}, "But before faith came, we were kept in custody under the law, confined for the faith which should afterwards be revealed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GAL 3:24"}, "So that the law has become our tutor to bring us to Masih, that we might be justified by faith.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GAL 3:25"}, "But now that faith has come, we are no longer under a tutor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GAL 3:26"}, "For you are all children of Allah, through faith in Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GAL 3:27"}, "For as many of you as were baptised into Masih have put on Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GAL 3:28"}, "There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither slave nor free man, there is neither male nor female; for you are all\none in Masih Isa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GAL 3:29"}, "If you are Masih\u2019s, then you are Ibrahim\u2019s offspring and heirs according to promise.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "GAL 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GAL 4:1"}, "But I say that so long as the heir is a child, he is no different from a bondservant, though he is lord of all,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GAL 4:2"}, "but is under guardians and stewards until the day appointed by the father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GAL 4:3"}, "So we also, when we were children, were held in bondage under the elemental principles of the world.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GAL 4:4"}, "But when the fullness of the time came, Allah sent out his Son, born to a woman, born under the law,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GAL 4:5"}, "that he might redeem those who were under the law, that we might receive the adoption of children.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GAL 4:6"}, "And because you are children, Allah sent out the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying,\n\u201cAbba,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Abba is a Greek spelling for the Aramaic word for \u201cFather\u201d or \u201cDaddy\u201d used in a familiar, respectful,\nand loving way. "]}], "caller": "+"}, " Father!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GAL 4:7"}, "So you are no longer a bondservant, but a son; and if a son, then an heir of Allah through Masih.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GAL 4:8"}, "However at that time, not knowing Allah, you were in bondage to those who by nature are not gods.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GAL 4:9"}, "But now that you have come to know Allah, or rather to be known by Allah, why do you turn back again to the weak and\nmiserable elemental principles, to which you desire to be in bondage all over again?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GAL 4:10"}, "You observe days, months, seasons, and years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GAL 4:11"}, "I am afraid for you, that I might have wasted my labour for you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GAL 4:12"}, "I beg you, brothers, become as I am, for I also have become as you are. You did me no wrong,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GAL 4:13"}, "but you know that because of weakness in the flesh I preached the Good News to you the first time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GAL 4:14"}, "That which was a temptation to you in my flesh, you didn\u2019t despise nor reject; but you received me as an angel of Allah,\neven as Masih Isa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GAL 4:15"}, "What was the blessing you enjoyed? For I testify to you that, if possible, you would have plucked out your eyes and given\nthem to me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GAL 4:16"}, "So then, have I become your enemy by telling you the truth?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GAL 4:17"}, "They zealously seek you in no good way. No, they desire to alienate you, that you may seek them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GAL 4:18"}, "But it is always good to be zealous in a good cause, and not only when I am present with you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GAL 4:19"}, "My little children, of whom I am again in travail until Masih is formed in you\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GAL 4:20"}, "but I could wish to be present with you now, and to change my tone, for I am perplexed about you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GAL 4:21"}, "Tell me, you that desire to be under the law, don\u2019t you listen to the law?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GAL 4:22"}, "For it is written that Ibrahim had two sons, one by the servant, and one by the free woman.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GAL 4:23"}, "However, the son by the servant was born according to the flesh, but the son by the free woman was born through promise.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GAL 4:24"}, "These things contain an allegory, for these are two covenants. One is from Mount Sinai, bearing children to bondage,\nwhich is Hajar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GAL 4:25"}, "For this Hajar is Mount Sinai in Arabia, and answers to the Jerusalem that exists now, for she is in bondage with her\nchildren. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GAL 4:26"}, "But the Jerusalem that is above is free, which is the mother of us all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GAL 4:27"}, "For it is written, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cRejoice, you barren who don\u2019t bear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Break out and shout, you who don\u2019t travail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For the desolate have more children than her who has a husband.\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 54:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GAL 4:28"}, "Now we, brothers, as Is\u1e25\u0101q was, are children of promise. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GAL 4:29"}, "But as then, he who was born according to the flesh persecuted him who was born according to the Spirit, so also it is\nnow. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GAL 4:30"}, "However what does the Scripture say? \u201cThrow out the servant and her son, for the son of the servant will not inherit with\nthe son of the free woman.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 21:10"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GAL 4:31"}, "So then, brothers, we are not children of a servant, but of the free woman.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "GAL 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GAL 5:1"}, "Stand firm therefore in the liberty by which Masih has made us free, and don\u2019t be entangled again with a yoke of bondage.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GAL 5:2"}, "Behold, I, Paul, tell you that if you receive circumcision, Masih will profit you nothing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GAL 5:3"}, "Yes, I testify again to every man who receives circumcision that he is a debtor to do the whole law.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GAL 5:4"}, "You are alienated from Masih, you who desire to be justified by the law. You have fallen away from grace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GAL 5:5"}, "For we, through the Spirit, by faith wait for the hope of righteousness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GAL 5:6"}, "For in Masih Isa neither circumcision amounts to anything, nor uncircumcision, but faith working through love.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GAL 5:7"}, "You were running well! Who interfered with you that you should not obey the truth?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GAL 5:8"}, "This persuasion is not from him who calls you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GAL 5:9"}, "A little yeast grows through the whole lump. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GAL 5:10"}, "I have confidence towards you in the Lord that you will think no other way. But he who troubles you will bear his\njudgement, whoever he is. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GAL 5:11"}, "But I, brothers, if I still preach circumcision, why am I still persecuted? Then the stumbling block of the cross has\nbeen removed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GAL 5:12"}, "I wish that those who disturb you would cut themselves off.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GAL 5:13"}, "For you, brothers, were called for freedom. Only don\u2019t use your freedom for gain to the flesh, but through love be\nservants to one another. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GAL 5:14"}, "For the whole law is fulfilled in one word, in this: \u201cYou shall love your neighbour as\nyourself.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["5:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Leviticus 19:18"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GAL 5:15"}, "But if you bite and devour one another, be careful that you don\u2019t consume one another.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GAL 5:16"}, "But I say, walk by the Spirit, and you won\u2019t fulfil the lust of the flesh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GAL 5:17"}, "For the flesh lusts against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh; and these are contrary to one another, that you\nmay not do the things that you desire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GAL 5:18"}, "But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GAL 5:19"}, "Now the deeds of the flesh are obvious, which are: adultery, sexual immorality, uncleanness, lustfulness,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GAL 5:20"}, "idolatry, sorcery, hatred, strife, jealousies, outbursts of anger, rivalries, divisions, heresies,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GAL 5:21"}, "envy, murders, drunkenness, orgies, and things like these; of which I forewarn you, even as I also forewarned you, that\nthose who practise such things will not inherit Allah\u2019s Kingdom.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GAL 5:22"}, "But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness,\nfaith,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, faithfulness"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GAL 5:23"}, "gentleness, and self-control. Against such things there is no law.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GAL 5:24"}, "Those who belong to Masih have crucified the flesh with its passions and lusts.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GAL 5:25"}, "If we live by the Spirit, let\u2019s also walk by the Spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GAL 5:26"}, "Let\u2019s not become conceited, provoking one another, and envying one another.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "GAL 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GAL 6:1"}, "Brothers, even if a man is caught in some fault, you who are spiritual must restore such a one in a spirit of gentleness;\nlooking to yourself so that you also aren\u2019t tempted. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GAL 6:2"}, "Bear one another\u2019s burdens, and so fulfil the law of Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GAL 6:3"}, "For if a man thinks himself to be something when he is nothing, he deceives himself.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GAL 6:4"}, "But let each man examine his own work, and then he will have reason to boast in himself, and not in someone else.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GAL 6:5"}, "For each man will bear his own burden. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GAL 6:6"}, "But let him who is taught in the word share all good things with him who teaches.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GAL 6:7"}, "Don\u2019t be deceived. Allah is not mocked, for whatever a man sows, that he will also reap.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GAL 6:8"}, "For he who sows to his own flesh will from the flesh reap corruption. But he who sows to the Spirit will from the Spirit\nreap eternal life. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GAL 6:9"}, "Let\u2019s not be weary in doing good, for we will reap in due season, if we don\u2019t give up.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GAL 6:10"}, "So then, as we have opportunity, let\u2019s do what is good towards all men, and especially towards those who are of the\nhousehold of the faith. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GAL 6:11"}, "See with what large letters I write to you with my own hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GAL 6:12"}, "As many as desire to make a good impression in the flesh compel you to be circumcised; just so they may not be persecuted\nfor the cross of Masih. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GAL 6:13"}, "For even they who receive circumcision don\u2019t keep the law themselves, but they desire to have you circumcised, that they\nmay boast in your flesh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GAL 6:14"}, "But far be it from me to boast, except in the cross of our Lord Al Masih Isa, through which the world has been crucified\nto me, and I to the world. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GAL 6:15"}, "For in Masih Isa neither is circumcision anything, nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GAL 6:16"}, "As many as walk by this rule, peace and mercy be on them, and on Allah\u2019s Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GAL 6:17"}, "From now on, let no one cause me any trouble, for I bear the marks of the Lord Isa branded on my body.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GAL 6:18"}, "The grace of our Lord Al Masih Isa be with your spirit, brothers. Amen.\n"]}]}